node.text:
Visit @SculptMovements 💕 for workouts, routine, and everythin else you eed to become fit! .
Treino de MMI com 01. Agachamento máquina 15/12/10 + drop com extensora 4 x 4 / 4x3 / 4x2 /4x 1 aumentando a carga ( 1 série ) 
1 x 10 com pico de contração em cima + 10 saindo da inércia 
1 x 10 com excêntrica lenta + 10 concêntrica lenta + 10 
02. Stiff 3 x 15 + bom dia 10 
03. Flexora 9 x 6 alternando a carga entre leva e pesado 
1 x 30 curtas + 10 isometria + 12 
1 x unilateral 8 /7/6 até zerar sem intervalo 
04. Flexora em pé 3 x 12 parando no meio + glúteo no cabo 3 x 12 
Panturrilhas sempre 😅
Macacão @santtaloren
.
.
.

node.text:
❌Circuit instructions❌

Perform each exercise for ⏰40 seconds

rest ONLY 15 seconds before moving onto the next exercise 😴 Rest 1 min after the last exercise. 🌀3 rounds total .credit : @anita_herbert
.
.
.
#Fitness #fitfam #fitspo #motivation #workout #workoutvideo #legday #gym #abs

🔥 FULL BODY🔥 Follow us (@GymGlutes) for the best daily workout tips 💪
••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
👋🏽!! Grab 2 Dumbbells and give this workout a go for a full body burn!🥵

🔺5 EXERCISES
🔺4 ROUNDS
🔺40 SEC WORK/ 20 SEC REST

➡️ SAVE FOR LATER & TAG A FRIEND⬅️

node.text:
🎈 PERIOD BLOAT 🎈Or let’s talk birth control. I was put on hormonal contraception when I was 14. 

Follow us (@GymGlutes) for the best daily workout tips 💪

I stayed on it for over 10 years. 

As a teen, it was to calm the extreme pain of my periods.

Later it was to keep my ex-partner happy; even though I wanted to be done with the stuff, he preferred birth control to anything else. 

These days I don’t take hormonal contraception. 

And after so many years of not having one, I’m fascinated by my period. 

My body BLOATS massively and RETAINS allll the WATER. 

My lower tummy swells. Aches. For a good 12 hours every cycle, I have extremely bad cramps and nausea. And then I become peaceful, sleepy, calm. 

It all feels, in its own way, powerful. Even as my body changes - or maybe because it does. 

So today, here, I just want to remind you:

It’s ok if your body fluctuates throughout the month. 

It’s ok if you don’t bloat one day and bloat like a beautiful balloon the next. 

It’s ok if you choose to use hormonal contraception. It’s equally ok if you choose not to. Just make sure that decision is yours and yours alone. 

It’s ok if you honour your body and listen to your body in a way that serves you. 

It’s ok if you do you. 

Period puffy or bloaty belly or in any way at all. 

You got this, you marvellous human. 
.
.
.
.
.
.

💥BE FIT - GLUTES💥
I ♥️ this training! You can do a hard workout at home to toned glutes muscles using ankle weights 😃

I did it with a 5 pounds weights
Try doing 3 rounds of each move 🙌🏻
Enjoy it 🔆
•
•
🇪🇸 BE FIT - GLÚTEOS💥
Este entrenamiento me gusta mucho ♥️ son 7 ejercicios para fortalecer los glúteos que puedes hacer en casa, usando las pesas de tobillos 😃

Yo lo hice con pesas de 5 libras
Les recomiendo hacer 3 series de cada ejercicio - los vídeos indican cuántas repeticiones por serie.
Espero que lo disfrutes 🔆
•
•
Credit @mariela.bravo.fit

node.text:
BEFORE AND NOW.
⁣⁣
Starting the international migueletes month with this super transformation from boring sad ☹️ to unbearable happy .😁 👙🛫⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Congratulations @flaviaplourenco, you said you were going to focus and really changed.
She entered the fight for the award for best student of the year 2020. 👏🏾👏🏾👏🏾👏🏾 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
You're boring, but you're cool too.
.
.
.
Credit: @saomiguelito #abworkout #coreworkout #quadsworkout #legworkout #gluteworkout #workoutvideos  #gymmotivation #bodybuilding #fitnessmotivation #homeworkout #fullbodyworkout #bodyweightworkout

node.text: Looking like a snack in @SculptSwim! 👙 Shop the end of summer sale and save 20% off with code ‘LABOUR20’

EPIC Glute / Leg Day 🍑  1 Dumbbell Only
-
SAVE + LIKE + SHARE + CRUSH IT 👊🏼 w My Crew 💚
-
So lucky to have been hooked up with a few dumbbells where I am staying at, on my birthday trip. I get to work out and enjoy this amazing view. So grateful🙏🏻🙌🏼
-
Workout deets, 8-12 reps for 3-4 sets:
1. Foot elevated lateral lunges
2. Hammie curls
3. Lunge step ups
4. Straddle sumo squats
5. Deficit RDLs
6. Froggers
7. Hip thrust
8. Box jump squats
-
Remember, mind-muscle connection 🧠 +💪🏼. It’s not how much you lift, but HOW you lift 😉
-
Last, but not least, Have Fun ☺️
-
-
-
Credit @senada.greca

node.text:
Coming at you with another band VS dumbbell since you guys loved the last one I posted! Follow us (@GymGlutes) for the best daily workout tips 💪

Today we’re working our shoulders & biceps because let’s not neglect our upper body okkk. ⁣
⁣
No matter where you are or what you’re working with, get that body movinggg because it feels good and ALSO I’m sure a lot of us need it for our mental health right now 🙏🏽⁣
⁣
Double tap & save for later ♥️⁣
⁣
Exercises:⁣
⁣
▫️Single arm shoulder press ⁣
▫️Front raises ⁣
▫️Hammer curls ⁣
▫️Bicep curls
⁣⁣
Credit: @chanelcocobrown 
#fitness #bodybuilding #gym #fitfam #motivation #tutorial
